Yeah, i certainly was. But i now realize how much more dangerous it is for that disorder to keep things in. An overactive mind with too many thoughts stuck inside is lethal .

Also i just talk about my condition in general, because so many dont know what it ‚Äò feels ‚Äò like. And i honestly had no idea i was any different than anyone else my age. Till i almost commited suicide. I had a support system there for me then to help me find out what was wrong.

I definitely have a different view on life in general now. As a kid i allowed my depression to consume me, i didnt have an outlet to share my feelings. Though i do now, and i have people who accept even my dark side. Though i dont have many issues since i started taking medicine.
Ive lived with bipolar disorder and depression for 10 years.
With a mental disability life is already hard enough to keep things straight with your own mind. No room for hate, lies and extra shit that you dont need. In my own case atleast.
